{
  "texts": [
    "In this Article, we show how human-AI interactions impact human cognition.",
    "In particular, we reveal that when humans repeatedly interact with biased AI systems, they learn to be more biased themselves.",
    "We show this in a range of domains and algorithms, including a widely used real-world text-to-image AI system.",
    "Modern AI systems rely on machine learning algorithms, such as convolutional neural networks 7 (CNNs) and transformers 8, to identify complex patterns in vast datasets, without requiring extensive explicit programming.",
    "These systems clearly augment human natural capabilities in a variety of domains, such as health care [9] [10] [11], education 12, marketing 13 and finance 14."
  ]
}